  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nConstans definitions should be more flexible, especially with usage of literal only  expressions such as:\r\n```\r\na: constant(uint256(wei)) = as_wei_value(1, \"ether\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nand\r\n\r\n```\r\nb: uint256 = 100 * 10 ** 16\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nThis will be a 3 stage process:\r\n\r\n- Move constant folding into it's own stage, as has been discussed as a refactoring step before (#1024)\r\n- Use constant folding on `constant()` definitions.\r\n- Allow as_wei_value to be used in constant definition.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n![](https://i.ytimg.com/vi/mFvnXWemY8o/maxresdefault.jpg)\r\n",
